text.tspan: Total COVID-19 tests conducted vs. confirmed cases
A high number of confirmed cases for a given level of testing suggests that confirmed cases are a large
underestimate of the total number of infections. Comparisons across countries are affected by differences in testing
Source: Testing data from official sources collated by Our World in Data, confirmed cases from Johns Hopkins University CSSE
